        "sanitize": false,
        "show": null,
        "text": "<p>Underground piping associated with aboveground oil storage tanks is regulated by the State Department of Environmental Protection (DEP) (207) 287-7688. Underground piping must be installed by a DEP Certified Installer. All underground piping associated with motor fuel tanks must be registered with the DEP. A permit is not required for a tank that is part of a listed generator unit. The unit must be installed according to the manufacturer&rsquo;s requirements. The capacity of a generator tank is counted for purposes of a Spill Prevention Control and Countermeasures Plan (SPCC).</p>",
